HEADWORD: mangosteen tree
<hw>mangosteen tree</hw> }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Malay
<ets>mangusta</ets>, <ets>mangis</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
tree of the East Indies of the genus <gen>Garcinia</gen> (<spn>Garcinia
Mangostana</spn>) with thick leathery leaves. The tree grows to the
height of eighteen feet, and bears fruit also called
<prod>mangosteen</prod>, of the size of a small apple, the pulp of which
is very delicious food.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

